p.k: A couple is torn between two dogs and can’t decide who to bring home with them. And, a local stray is in dire need of medical attention, but afraid of humans
A phone call in the middle of the night leads Tia racing to deal with a family emergency. And, a homeless man reaches out for help when his dog has trouble breathing
Moe and Lizzy rescue a sick stray, but a diagnosis proves tricky. Meanwhile, new mom Tania struggles to find a balance between life and work at Villalobos
The rescue team begin Operation Rhino, hoping to place a long-term shelter resident in a fantastic home. Plus, two dogs need rescuing in the French Quarter
The crew rescues a sick and injured dog that is facing a whole host of difficult health problems. Plus, former parolee worker Matt returns to the shelter
Overwhelmed by work, Tia hires three new parolees to help out – but soon things take a turn for the worse. And the shelter is swamped by a group of new dogs
73% Dr. Kate investigates why a rabbit has stopped eating. Plus, a sausage dog receives experimental treatment and Dr. Peter helps a monkey with suspected tuberculosis
Dr Ross takes care of a pair of roosters involved in a barnyard brawl and joins Dr Lavigne for a hyena consultation. And, Dr Blue treats a paralysed Yorkie
With thousands of animals in need, and vet care unaffordable to most, Dr Jeff heads to Mexico to run a mobile clinic and help as many people and pets as they can
In a remote corner of the Indian Ocean, Reunion Island has become the most dangerous place on the planet for shark attacks. Is there a way of preventing them?
Villalobos throws a Halloween party to raise money for the rescue. An old friend returns and Lizzy struggles to rescue a stray dog in the middle of the night
Jon Frankel meets the marine biologist who is convinced that mermaids exist and examines the social media response to apparent sightings of the mythical creature
Top scientists reveal how a revolutionary study and advanced DNA technology solved the mystery of the legendary Loch Ness monster

p.n: The Lost Kingdom Of The Yeti
p.k: In the high-altitude wilderness of Bhutan, new evidence hints that the mysterious yeti may exist. Mark Evans travels into the Himalayas to discover the truth
Dusty and the team must capture a giant calf-eating snake and venture into an abandoned factory to save upper Florida from invasive pythons
Follows the story of an American scientist who was convicted of killing and cannibalizing two colleagues in the jungles of Flores, Indonesia in 1977
The Raneys are faced with the daunting task of overhauling a faulty electrical system and building the first hydro-electric wheel on the Little Susitna River
A family asks Pete to build a brewery-in-the-sky on their massive property. Pete crafts a barn themed tavern with a brewing system in the trees accessible by a rope
An Irish family has the perfect tree to nestle a Celtic-themed cottage. Pete devises a design that includes a rainmaker to mimic the wet Ireland climate
Pete builds an adventure-themed treehouse for a family of explorers in Pennsylvania’s Pocono Mountains. This two-storey masterpiece is packed with novelties
How do caterpillars transform into magnificent butterflies in their cocoon? Plus, why are cats’ tongues the way they are? Experts answer these questions and more!
